cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.SOC, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the potential of social networking sites for science and proposes a bi-directional model for linking SNSs to scholarly DLs. This involves enhancing retrieval quality at DL side by social information provided by SNSs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Other likely categories include cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
